## Background

asupersync's core invariant: **Cancellation is a protocol, not silent drop.**

When I/O operations are cancelled:
1. Registrations must be cleaned up
2. No leaked obligations
3. No dangling wakers
4. Resources properly released

## Cancellation Tests

### Cancel During Read

