Implement an adapter that wraps an AsupersyncService to be used as a Tower Service.

## Challenge: Cx Provider

Tower Services don't receive a Cx. We need a mechanism to provide one.

### Option 1: Thread-local Cx
```rust
thread_local! {
    static CURRENT_CX: Cell<Option<&'static Cx>> = Cell::new(None);
}
```
Pro: Simple, no overhead
Con: Only works within asupersync runtime

### Option 2: Cx Provider trait
```rust
pub trait CxProvider: Send + Sync {
    fn current_cx(&self) -> &Cx;
}
```
Pro: Flexible, testable
Con: Requires configuration

### Recommendation: Option 2 with default thread-local implementation

## Adapter Design

```rust
/// Wraps an AsupersyncService as a Tower Service.
/// 
/// # Cx Resolution
/// 
/// Since Tower Services don't receive a Cx, this adapter uses
/// a CxProvider to obtain one. The default provider uses the
/// thread-local Cx set by the runtime.
/// 
/// # Example
/// ```
/// struct MyService;
/// impl AsupersyncService<Request> for MyService { ... }
/// 
/// let tower_service = TowerAdapter::new(MyService);
/// 
/// // Use with Tower middleware
/// let service = tower::ServiceBuilder::new()
///     .rate_limit(100, Duration::from_secs(1))
///     .service(tower_service);
/// ```
pub struct TowerAdapter<S, P = ThreadLocalCxProvider> {
    inner: S,
    cx_provider: P,
}

impl<S> TowerAdapter<S, ThreadLocalCxProvider> {
    /// Create adapter using thread-local Cx.
    pub fn new(service: S) -> Self {
        Self {
            inner: service,
            cx_provider: ThreadLocalCxProvider,
        }
    }
}

impl<S, P> TowerAdapter<S, P> {
    /// Create adapter with custom Cx provider.
    pub fn with_provider(service: S, provider: P) -> Self {
        Self {
            inner: service,
            cx_provider: provider,
        }
    }
}
```

## Tower Service Implementation

```rust
impl<S, P, Request> tower::Service<Request> for TowerAdapter<S, P>
where
    S: AsupersyncService<Request> + Clone,
    P: CxProvider,
    Request: Send + 'static,
{
    type Response = S::Response;
    type Error = S::Error;
    type Future = TowerAdapterFuture<S, Request>;

    fn poll_ready(&mut self, _cx: &mut Context<'_>) -> Poll<Result<(), Self::Error>> {
        // Asupersync services are always ready (backpressure via budgets)
        Poll::Ready(Ok(()))
    }

    fn call(&mut self, request: Request) -> Self::Future {
        let service = self.inner.clone();
        let cx = self.cx_provider.current_cx();

        TowerAdapterFuture {
            inner: Box::pin(async move {
                service.call(cx, request).await
            }),
        }
    }
}
